Scotland &apos; s independent schools have a track record of academic excellence that has continued in 2018 with another set of outstanding results in examinations, which is further enhanced by individual and collective success in sport, the arts, music and other community projects.
With over 30,000 pupils in every corner of Scotland, these centres, represented by the Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS), are striving to deliver the best possible service to pupils and parents.
Independent schools are designed to prepare their students for further education, for the career they choose and for the place they will occupy as citizens of the world.
As an educational sector that can design and implement an adapted curriculum, modern languages are still popular and desired subjects in schools.
As Nelson Mandela said, &quot; If you talk to a man in a language he understands, he will listen to you.
